caption.paragraph:
FIGURE 28.

Ithyphenes australiensis


sp. nov.

, orig. A–D, F–H: holotype, male from NSW (“3 km N of Landsowne …”); E, I: paratype from QLD (“… Cape Tribulation…”); 
A
: body, dorsal; 
B
: head, dorsal; 
C
: head, ventral; 
D
: thorax, ventral; 
E
: terminal abdominal segment, ventral; 
F
: male anal sclerite, ventral; 
G
: tegmen, ventral; 
H
: penis trunk, dorsal; 
I
: ovipositor, ventral. Scale bars: 
a
= 1.0 mm to Fig. A; 
b
= 0.5 mm to Figs B–E; 
с
= 0.25 mm to Figs F–I.
